description:
## Problem
Writers returning after a break lose momentum because the app can reopen a story, but does not quickly restore narrative intent, last decisions, and next action for the specific scene. This restart tax slows completion.

## Target user
Writers drafting in short sessions who frequently pause and resume across days or devices.

## Outcome / KPI
- Reduce time-to-first-edit after opening a story
- Increase % of sessions that produce edits within first 3 minutes
- Improve multi-session continuity (returning users continue the intended next scene)

## Scope
- Add optional end-session handoff note prompt tied to the active scene (what changed, what is next)
- Add `Resume context` card when reopening a story: last edited scene, last handoff note, unresolved revision queue items, and next planned action
- Add one-click `Resume this scene` action that navigates to exact scene and cursor position when available
- Allow dismissing or snoozing resume card without deleting handoff history
- Keep per-story timeline of recent handoff notes (latest 10) for continuity reference

## Non-goals
- AI-generated summaries of entire manuscript
- Team handoff workflows for multi-author collaboration
- Calendar/reminder notification system

## Acceptance criteria
- Writer can save an end-session handoff note in under 20 seconds
- Reopening the story shows resume context with last scene and note
- `Resume this scene` navigates to the correct scene and restores cursor when data exists
- Resume card can be snoozed/dismissed and re-opened from story workspace
- Recent handoff history persists per story across reloads

## Priority rationale
Living Writer-inspired organization is necessary, but session-to-session continuity is where writer flow is won or lost. This feature directly supports finishing behavior by reducing restart friction in everyday drafting.

## Handoff
Assign to: Market Research

<plan>

## Goal

Add session handoff notes and one-click resume context to the story editor so writers can capture end-of-session intent and instantly restore that context when returning to a story.

## Scope and files

**New files:**
- `src/types/handoff.ts` — HandoffNote + SessionState types
- `src/lib/handoff.ts` — localStorage/sessionStorage CRUD
- `src/components/HandoffNoteModal/HandoffNoteModal.tsx`
- `src/components/HandoffNoteModal/HandoffNoteModal.module.css`
- `src/components/ResumeContextCard/ResumeContextCard.tsx`
- `src/components/ResumeContextCard/ResumeContextCard.module.css`
- `src/components/HandoffHistory/HandoffHistory.tsx`
- `src/components/HandoffHistory/HandoffHistory.module.css`

**Modified files:**
- `src/app/story/[id]/page.tsx` — add state, ref, "End session" button, ResumeContextCard, HandoffHistory, HandoffNoteModal
- `src/app/story/[id]/page.module.css` — new layout classes
- `src/app/page.tsx` — enrich Quick Resume card with session data
- `src/app/page.module.css` — Quick Resume session data styles

## Step-by-step plan

### Phase 1: Types (`src/types/handoff.ts`)

```ts
export interface HandoffNote {
  id: string;                   // crypto.randomUUID()
  storyId: string;
  sceneId: string | null;       // null when no active scene
  sceneTitle: string | null;
  whatChanged: string;          // "" when skipped
  whatIsNext: string;           // "" when skipped
  createdAt: string;            // ISO 8601
}

export interface SessionState {
  storyId: string;
  lastEditedSceneId: string | null;
  lastEditedSceneTitle: string | null;
  lastEditorScrollTop: number;
  lastEditorCursorOffset: number;
  lastHandoffNoteId: string | null;
  updatedAt: string;            // ISO 8601
}
```

### Phase 2: Handoff lib (`src/lib/handoff.ts`)

localStorage keys (all per-story):
- `story-${storyId}-handoff-notes` → `HandoffNote[]`, capped at 10 (newest-first, prepend + slice)
- `story-${storyId}-session` → `SessionState`
- `handoff-recent-story` → `{ storyId: string; title: string; sessionUpdatedAt: string }` (latest story for home page)

sessionStorage key (tab-scoped snooze):
- `story-${storyId}-resume-dismissed` → `"true"`

Exported functions:
```ts
saveHandoffNote(storyId: string, note: Omit<HandoffNote, 'id' | 'createdAt'>): HandoffNote
getHandoffNotes(storyId: string): HandoffNote[]
getLatestHandoffNote(storyId: string): HandoffNote | null
saveSessionState(storyId: string, state: Omit<SessionState, 'updatedAt'>, storyTitle: string): void
getSessionState(storyId: string): SessionState | null
setResumeCardSnoozed(storyId: string): void
isResumeCardSnoozed(storyId: string): boolean
getRecentStory(): { storyId: string; title: string; sessionUpdatedAt: string } | null
```

Implementation notes:
- All functions guard `typeof window === 'undefined'` at top (SSR safety)
- `saveHandoffNote`: prepend to array, `array.slice(0, 10)`, persist
- `saveSessionState`: builds full `SessionState` with `updatedAt: new Date().toISOString()`, persists, also writes `handoff-recent-story`
- Parse errors: `try/catch` returns safe defaults (null / [])

### Phase 3: HandoffNoteModal component

**`HandoffNoteModal.tsx`**

Props:
```ts
interface Props {
  storyId: string;
  activeSceneId: string | null;
  activeSceneTitle: string | null;
  onSave: (note: HandoffNote) => void;
  onDismiss: () => void;
}
```

Layout (fixed bottom-right panel):
1. Header row: `<h2 id="handoff-modal-title">End session</h2>` + close `<button>` (flex row, space-between)
2. If `activeSceneTitle`: `<p className={styles.sceneIndicator}>Active scene: {activeSceneTitle}</p>`
3. `<label htmlFor="what-changed">What changed?</label>` + `<textarea id="what-changed" rows={3} />`
4. `<label htmlFor="whats-next">What's next?</label>` + `<input id="whats-next" type="text" />`
5. Actions: `<button onClick={handleSave}>Save note</button>` + `<button onClick={onDismiss}>Skip</button>`

Behavior:
- `useRef<HTMLTextAreaElement>(null)` for whatChanged field; `useEffect(() => { ref.current?.focus() }, [])` on mount
- Focus trap: `onKeyDown` on outer div — when Tab/Shift+Tab would leave the panel, redirect to first/last interactive element
- `onKeyDown` on outer div: Escape → `onDismiss()`
- `handleSave`: calls `saveHandoffNote(storyId, { sceneId: activeSceneId, sceneTitle: activeSceneTitle, whatChanged, whatIsNext })`, calls `onSave(note)`

ARIA: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-labelledby="handoff-modal-title"` on outer div

**`HandoffNoteModal.module.css`**

