### Phase 4: ResumeContextCard component

**`ResumeContextCard.tsx`**

Props:
```ts
interface Props {
  session: SessionState;
  latestNote: HandoffNote | null;
  onResume: (sceneId: string | null, scrollTop: number, cursorOffset: number) => void;
  onDismiss: () => void;
  onSnooze: () => void;
}
```

Layout (horizontal flex banner):
```tsx
<div role="region" aria-label="Resume context" className={styles.card}>
  <div className={styles.content}>
    {session.lastEditedSceneTitle && (
      <span className={styles.label}>Last scene: <strong>{session.lastEditedSceneTitle}</strong></span>
    )}
    {latestNote?.whatChanged && <span className={styles.noteRow}>Changed: {latestNote.whatChanged}</span>}
    {latestNote?.whatIsNext  && <span className={styles.noteRow}>Next: {latestNote.whatIsNext}</span>}
  </div>
  <div className={styles.actions}>
    <button className={styles.resumeButton} onClick={() => onResume(session.lastEditedSceneId, session.lastEditorScrollTop, session.lastEditorCursorOffset)}>
      Resume this scene
    </button>
    <button className={styles.actionLink} onClick={onSnooze}>Snooze</button>
    <button className={styles.actionLink} onClick={onDismiss}>Dismiss</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

When `session.lastEditedSceneId` is null, "Resume this scene" is still shown but just calls `onResume(null, scrollTop, cursorOffset)` — page restores scroll/cursor only.

