## Test plan

**Build check** (required, zero errors):
```
npm run build
```

**Manual tests — Handoff capture:**
- Open any story in editor view
- "End session" button is visible in header actions row
- Click "End session" → modal appears fixed bottom-right, focus on "What changed?" textarea
- Press Escape → modal closes without saving
- Tab/Shift+Tab cycles only within modal
- Fill both fields, click "Save note" → modal closes, sidebar shows note at top
- Click "Skip" → modal closes without saving

**Manual tests — Resume context card:**
- First visit to a story: no resume card visible
- Edit textarea, blur away (Tab out or click elsewhere) → session saved to localStorage
- Close tab, reopen same story URL → resume card visible below editor header
- Inspect localStorage key `story-${id}-session` to verify scroll + cursor offset
- Click "Resume this scene" → card hides, editor scrolled/focused
- Click "Snooze" → card hides; open same story in new tab → card reappears (sessionStorage cleared)
- Click "Dismiss" → card hides; open same story in new tab → card reappears (only sessionStorage cleared)

**Manual tests — HandoffHistory sidebar:**
- 0 notes: shows "No session notes yet"
- 3 notes saved: shows newest-first with relative times
- Save 11 notes: only 10 appear (cap enforced)

**Manual tests — Home Quick Resume:**
- With session data: "Next: ..." text visible below timestamp
- Without handoff notes: no "Next:" row shown (graceful null case)

**Accessibility checks:**
- VoiceOver: dialog announced on modal open, "Resume context" region announced
- All buttons have text or aria-label
- Tab through modal confirms focus trap works
- WCAG AA color contrast verified for new text styles

## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| `--shadow-lg` / `--z-modal` / `--font-size-xs` tokens may not exist | Inline fallback values in CSS noted per component |
| Cursor offset invalid if content changed since last session | Acceptable v1; silently fails gracefully (setSelectionRange clamps to content length) |
| sessionStorage snooze lost on tab close | Intentional per-tab behavior per spec |
| Modal z-index conflicts with other fixed elements | z-index fallback 100 is above all current fixed elements |

## Rollback strategy

All changes are additive. To disable: remove "End session" button from JSX. `ResumeContextCard` is null-guarded. `HandoffHistory` reverts to placeholder div. Home page note preview is conditional. No migrations required.

## Observability

- `saveHandoffNote` and `getSessionState` should not add new console.log (remove any debug logs before commit, consistent with BIN-73 fix)
- Session tracking fires on textarea `onBlur` — no performance impact
- Future: instrument `end_session_note_saved` + `resume_scene_clicked` events when analytics added

## Acceptance mapping

| Acceptance criterion | Covered by |
|---|---|
| Save handoff note in under 20 seconds | Phase 3: two optional fields, one-click Save |
| Reopening shows resume context with last scene and note | Phases 4, 6 |
| "Resume this scene" navigates and restores cursor | Phase 6 `handleResumeScene` |
| Resume card snoozable/dismissable without deleting history | Phase 4 sessionStorage snooze + Dismiss state |
| Handoff history persists per story across reloads | Phases 2, 5 localStorage |

