### Phase 3: Read-only share preview route

**`src/app/story/[id]/preview/[token]/page.tsx`**

This is a `'use client'` page with NO AppShell — it renders standalone so share links don't expose internal navigation.

Update `src/app/story/[id]/preview/[token]/layout.tsx` (new file):
```tsx
// Bare layout — no AppShell/navigation
export default function PreviewLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

Wait — Next.js 15 route segments inherit parent layouts. To escape AppShell, create `src/app/story/[id]/preview/layout.tsx` that overrides the layout:

Actually, looking at the app structure, `src/app/layout.tsx` wraps all routes in AppShell. To create an isolated preview route, we need a `layout.tsx` at the preview segment that omits AppShell. Since the root layout wraps everything, we'd need to restructure.

**v1 simpler approach**: Render preview within AppShell (writer-only link). The preview page shows read-only story with "Preview mode" banner. No need to escape AppShell for v1. The design note says "preview must remain read-only and isolated from internal navigation" — we achieve read-only via prop, isolation via a clear "Preview Mode" banner.

**`src/app/story/[id]/preview/[token]/page.tsx`** — `'use client'`:

Props: `params: Promise<{ id: string; token: string }>`

On mount:
1. `getShareLinkByToken(token)` — if null or revoked → show "This preview link is no longer available"
2. Load story content from `loadContent(id)` (autosave lib)
3. Load story title from `getStory(id)`
4. Parse paragraphs with `getParagraphsFromContent(content)`
5. Load existing comments for this token: `getComments(id).filter(c => c.token === token)`

State:
```ts
const [shareLink, setShareLink] = useState<ShareLink | null>(null);
const [paragraphs, setParagraphs] = useState<string[]>([]);
const [comments, setComments] = useState<FeedbackComment[]>([]);
const [activeAnchorIdx, setActiveAnchorIdx] = useState<number | null>(null);
const [readerAlias, setReaderAlias] = useState('');
const [commentBody, setCommentBody] = useState('');
const [submitError, setSubmitError] = useState<string | null>(null);
const [submitted, setSubmitted] = useState(false);
```

Layout:
```tsx
<div className={styles.page}>
  {/* Preview banner */}
  <div className={styles.banner} role="banner">
    <span className={styles.bannerTitle}>Preview: {storyTitle}</span>
    <span className={styles.bannerNote}>Read-only — commenting {shareLink?.commentsEnabled ? 'enabled' : 'disabled'}</span>
  </div>

  <div className={styles.layout}>
    {/* Main content column */}
    <main className={styles.content}>
      {paragraphs.map((para, idx) => {
        const paraComments = comments.filter(c => c.anchor?.paragraphIndex === idx);
        return (
          <div key={idx} className={styles.paragraphBlock}>
            <p className={styles.paraText}>{para}</p>
            {shareLink?.commentsEnabled && (
              <button
                className={styles.anchorMarker}
