## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Web Crypto `subtle` unavailable in non-HTTPS contexts | App runs on localhost (dev) or HTTPS (prod) — SubtleCrypto always available. Add `typeof crypto.subtle !== 'undefined'` guard and disable sync with error if missing |
| Passphrase entry inline (no modal) may feel unusual | Design brief calls for avoiding modals on mobile — inline approach is correct; clear label ("Enter your passphrase to back up") makes purpose obvious |
| Mock sync (localStorage) doesn't actually provide cross-device sync | Clearly documented in v1 code comments; future sprint replaces with real API calls |
| ConflictPanel `role="alert"` + `aria-live="assertive"` may announce too aggressively | Acceptable for conflict resolution which requires user attention |
| `settings/page.tsx` becomes client component — SSR loss | Settings is user-specific interactive content; client rendering is correct here |

## Rollback strategy

All changes are additive except converting `settings/page.tsx` to `'use client'`. To revert: change `settings/page.tsx` back to server component (remove SyncSettings import and section). Story page additions are null-guarded. No data migrations.

## Observability

- No console.log in production code
- `setupSync`, `syncStory`, `downloadStory` should log errors via `console.error` only on failure
- Future: instrument `sync_enabled`, `sync_completed`, `conflict_resolved` events

