**Build check:**
```
npm run build
```
Zero TypeScript errors required.

**Manual tests — Consent flow:**
- Open Settings → "AI & Privacy" section visible
- Consent card shown with policy list, unchecked checkbox
- Checkbox unchecked → "Enable AI features" button disabled
- Check checkbox → button enabled
- Click "Enable AI features" → consent card replaced by "Granted on [date]" row; global toggle shown
- "Revoke consent" → consent card returns; all per-story overrides cleared

**Manual tests — Global toggle:**
- Toggle off → all stories inherit "Off" status
- Toggle on → stories inherit "On" status

**Manual tests — Per-story panel:**
- Open story editor → sidebar has "AI" section showing badge reflecting global state
- On mobile (<1024px): inline AI panel shows above editor canvas; sidebar "AI" section hidden
- Change story override to "Always on for this story" → badge updates immediately
- Change to "Always off" → badge shows "Overridden off"

**Manual tests — Activity log:**
- No AI calls yet → "No AI actions yet" empty state shown
- Manually call `logAiActivity(...)` in browser console → entry appears in list
- After 21 entries: only 20 shown (cap enforced)

**Manual tests — AI gating:**
- `isAiEnabled(storyId)` returns false when no consent
- `isAiEnabled` returns per-story override when set
- All future AI UI should call `isAiEnabled` before rendering AI action buttons

**Accessibility:**
- Checkbox in consent card labeled via wrapping `<label>`
- Toggle switch: `role="switch"` on input, `aria-label` on wrapping label
- Settings section heading: `aria-labelledby` on section, `id` on h2
- Select in AiStoryPanel: `aria-label="AI setting for this story"`
- Focus: all interactive elements have visible 2px focus ring

## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Settings page `settingsGroup` has `groupContent` with centered flex — need alignment fix for AI section | Use `settingsGroup` without `groupContent` wrapper for AI section, or pass `align-items: flex-start` inline |
| CSS toggle switch may appear inconsistent across browsers | Uses standard `accent-color` on checkbox for simplest cross-browser support; pure CSS slider is only decorative |
| No AI endpoints exist yet | Correct — this is infrastructure only. `isAiEnabled()` is the gate; no actual API calls in scope |
| `revokeConsent()` clearing all per-story configs requires iterating all stories | Simpler: iterate `getStories()` and call `localStorage.removeItem('ai-story-config-' + s.id)` |

## Rollback strategy

All additive. Remove AiPrivacySettings from settings page and AiStoryPanel from story page to disable. No data migrations.

## Observability

- No console.log in new code
- `grantConsent()` and `revokeConsent()` timing captured in `AiConsentConfig.consentedAt` for future analytics

## Acceptance mapping

| Acceptance criterion | Covered by |
|---|---|
| AI unavailable until explicit opt-in | Phase 2 `isAiEnabled()` gates all AI actions + Phase 3 consent gate UI |
| Disable AI globally and per story, changes apply immediately | Phase 2 `setGlobalEnabled()` + `setStoryOverride()` with immediate state sync |
| Data-use notice visible before first AI use and in Settings | Phase 3 consent card policy list + link from AiStoryPanel |
| Last 20 AI actions shown | Phase 2 `logAiActivity()` cap + Phase 3 activity list component |
| Disabled AI fails safely with clear message | AiStoryPanel shows "AI features require consent" + Settings link |

